# EKW-PASS Project Context

Rebuilt from a legacy DOS (CA-Clipper/dBASE) automotive repair shop ERP called E.K.W.-PASS.

## Architecture

- **Backend**: Go 1.25, Gin framework, pgx v5 driver, JWT auth (golang-jwt/v5)
- **Frontend**: React 18, TypeScript, Vite 5, Tailwind CSS 3, React Router v6, TanStack Query v5, Axios
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 16 with UUID primary keys, multi-tenant via `shop_id` on every table
- **Deployment**: Docker Compose (db, backend, frontend via nginx)

## Project Layout

```
backend/
  cmd/server/main.go              # Entry point
  internal/config/                # Env-based config (DatabaseURL, JWTSecret, Port)
  internal/database/              # pgxpool connection + golang-migrate migrations
  internal/middleware/            # JWT auth, CORS, tenant scoping
  internal/models/                # One file per entity, json:"camelCase" tags
  internal/repositories/          # pgx parameterized queries, context-first, shop_id scoped
  internal/services/              # Business logic layer
  internal/handlers/              # Gin HTTP handlers + router.go wiring
  migrations/                     # SQL migration files (000001_initial_schema)
frontend/
  src/api/                        # Axios client + per-entity API modules
  src/hooks/useAuth.tsx           # AuthContext with JWT in localStorage
  src/components/layout/          # AppLayout (sidebar + header + Outlet), Sidebar
  src/pages/                      # Route-level page components
  src/types/index.ts              # TypeScript interfaces matching Go models
```

## Key Design Decisions

- **Multi-tenant**: Every table has `shop_id` FK; all queries filter by it
- **Auth flow**: GET /api/auth/status checks initialization; POST /api/auth/setup creates first shop+admin; POST /api/auth/login returns JWT (24h expiry)
- **Roles**: admin, technician, front_desk
- **IDs**: UUID v4 generated before INSERT (uuid.New())
- **Dates**: *time.Time for nullable dates, time.Time for required timestamps
- **Money**: float64 in Go / number in TypeScript (NUMERIC in PostgreSQL)
- **Errors**: c.JSON(status, gin.H{"error": "message"})

## Database Schema (16 tables)

shops, users, customers, vehicles, suppliers, parts, work_orders, work_order_technicians, work_order_lines, sales, ar_transactions, ap_transactions, recalls, lookup_codes, audit_logs, shop_settings

## Legacy Source (read-only reference)

`old_version/Ekwpass/` contains the original DBF data files and structure definitions (e.g., CUSTOMER.151, VEHICLE.166). No source code (.PRG) exists -- schema was reverse-engineered from DBF field descriptors and error logs.

## Canadian Tax System

GST (federal) + PST (provincial) or HST (combined). Per-customer tax exemptions. Rates stored in shop_settings. Tax calculation happens during work order finalization.

